The paper discusses advanced receiver architectures for millimeter wave communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of low-resolution ADCs and hybrid analog-and-digital beamforming also involves signal processing and control systems (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on millimeter wave communications, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper introduces a receiver with learning-based detection, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
